quran[16]{c,v,t,f}:
  55,58,"(In beauty) they are like rubies and coral."
  55,59,"Then which of the Blessings of your Lord will you both (jinn and men) deny?"
  55,60,"Is there any reward for good other than good?"
  56,49,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  56,50,""
  56,51,""
  61,13,"And also (He will give you) another (blessing) which you love, - help from Allâh (against your enemies) and a near victory. And give glad tidings (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) to the believers."
  61,14,"O you who believe! Be you helpers (in the Cause) of Allâh as said ‘Îsâ (Jesus), son of Maryam (Mary), to the Hawâriyyûn (the disciples): "
  62,10,"Then when the (Jumu‘ah) Salât (prayer) is ended, you may disperse through the land, and seek the Bounty of Allâh (by working, etc.), and remember Allâh much: that you may be successful."
  62,11,"And when they see some merchandise or some amusement [beating of Tambur (drum) etc.] they disperse headlong to it, and leave you (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) standing [while delivering Jumu‘ah religious talk (Khutbah)]. Say: "
  63,7,"They are the ones who say: "
  63,8,"They (hyprocrites) say: "
  63,9,"O you who believe! Let not your properties or your children divert you from the remembrance of Allâh. And whosoever does that, then they are the losers."
  64,1,"Whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is on the earth glorifies Allâh. His is the dominion, and to Him belong all the praises and thanks, and He is Able to do all things."
  64,2,"He it is Who created you, then some of you are disbelievers and some of you are believers. And Allâh is All-Seer of what you do."
  64,3,"He has created the heavens and the earth with truth, and He shaped you and made good your shapes. And to Him is the final Return."